    <h3>Discussion Questions:</h3>
<p><em>(To make sure all students participate, you may want to break the class into groups of 5 to 8 students. Appoint one student in each group to take notes and report results to the class. Consider using that feedback for future bullying prevention projects.)</em></p>
<ul>
  <li>What are some of the reasons teens don&rsquo;t tell an adult?</li>
  <li>What can schools do to help prevent bullying?</li>
  <li>What can parents do to be helpful? </li>
  <li>What is not helpful?</li>
</ul>
